'''Ethics''' is a general term for what is often described as the "[[science]](study) of [[morality]]". In [[philosophy]], ethical [[behavior]] is that which is "[[Goodness and value theory|good]]" or "right." The Western tradition of ethics is sometimes called '''moral philosophy'''. This is one part of [[value theory]] ([[axiology]]) -- the other part is aesthetics -- of the four major branches of philosophy, alongside [[metaphysics]], [[epistemology]], and [[logic]].
